=Description=

"The Creating Bioregional Funding Ecosystems three-part series takes a candid, pragmatic, and in-depth look at the theory and practice of funding regenerative work in bioregions. 

Part 1 is "A Systemic Exploration." It features a presentation by Samantha Power, formerly with The World Bank and now Founder of Finance for Gaia, followed by material from Joe Brewer, Co-Founder of the Design School for Regenerating Earth.

...

How can we create financial structures and systems to fund the vital bioregional regeneration required? Of course, funding isn't an isolated topic. In practical terms, each bioregion needs three key pillars: Bioregional Learning Center (the keystone structure), a Portfolio of Projects (both social and ecological regeneration), and a Bioregional Foundation (which supports a funding ecosystem, regenerative economy, and governance)."



